25. In the figure below, ΔABC and ΔBAD are right triangles such that ∠ABC ≌ ∠BAD, ∠C ≌ ∠D, and AB ≌ AB. Which of the following congruence criteria applies directly to show that ΔABC ≌ ΔBAD?(Note: The symbol ≌ means "is congruent to.")

choices.A: AAS (If 2 angles of a triangle and the side opposite one of those angles are congruent to the corresponding parts of another triangle, then the triangles are congruent.)
choices.B: HL (If the hypotenuse and 1 leg of a right triangle are congruent to the corresponding parts of another right triangle, then the triangles are congruent.)
choices.C: LL(If the 2 legs of a right triangle are congruent to the corresponding parts of another right triangle, then the triangles are congruent.)
choices.D: SAS (If 2 sides and the included angle of a triangle are congruent to the corresponding parts  of another triangle, then the triangles are congruent.)
choices.E: SSS (If 3 sides of a triangle are congruent to the corresponding parts of another triangle, then the triangles are congruent. )
